                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/991</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_BTH1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Birch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-26T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>252. Report present status of enemy firms Portugal on British statutory list and
                    actual progress made by Portuguese Government <pb facs="0192" n="1026"
                        xml:id="pg_1026"/> in liquidating enemy interest therein. Prepare to report
                    on such houses or other enemy firms for inclusion American enemy trading list.
                    Proper to informally intimate to Portuguese Government such American listing
                    under consideration unless definite assurance received prompt liquidation by
                    present Government of enemy interest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
